# POPIS Hackathon Boilerplate - Environment Setup Guide
# =====================================================
#
# This repository uses separate environment files for frontend and backend:
#
# Backend Environment:
#   Location: backend/.env
#   Copy from: backend/.env.example
#   Usage: Backend configuration (port, database, etc.)
#
# Frontend Environment:
#   Location: frontend/.env.local
#   Copy from: frontend/.env.example
#   Usage: Frontend configuration (API URL, public variables)
#
# Quick Setup:
# ------------
# 1. Copy backend/.env.example to backend/.env
# 2. Copy frontend/.env.example to frontend/.env.local
# 3. Modify values as needed for your environment
#
# Docker users: The default values work out of the box!
# Just run: docker-compose up
#
# Local development users: Ensure ports 3000 and 3001 are available
